data.description: Quintessential historic colonial farmhouse on 5.2 acres within highly sought after Burnt Hills Ballston Lake School District.  This 5 bedroom, 3 full baths, 3392 sq ft home is full of character and charm with its wide plank fir flooring in 2/3 of the home, a keeping room, library, spacious formal dining and living rooms, and dual staircases. Home is the Colonial Inn/Tavern mentioned in the book, War on Middleline, and is where General George Washington stayed! So cool to imagine! Lots of fruit bushes on the property for pies and jams. Nice In-Law suite generating vacation rental income covering all taxes plus some. Three story Barn with huge workshop and plenty of storage space was repointed and supported in 2016. Barn as is, not to be included in inspection
